# USER.md — Stark's Preferences & Working Style
Set once. Every agent reads this. You stop explaining yourself every session.
Update any section whenever your preferences change.

---

## About You
Name: Stark
Role: Sole founder and operator of YVON (parent company)
Ventures: Novizio (fashion brand), Hourbour (financial app)
Context: Running both brands solo — you wear every hat. Efficiency and clarity over completeness.

---

## Monday Protocol (do this every Monday, 10 minutes)
This is the most important thing in this file. Without it, every agent flies blind.

Fill in the "Current Focus" section every Monday before the first session:
Primary venture this week — Novizio or Hourbour. Pick one. Not both.
Active project — the one thing In Flight right now
Top blocker — the one thing standing between you and shipping
Not focused on this week — explicitly name what you're ignoring. Helps agents avoid irrelevant suggestions.

---

## How You Like to Work

### Output Format
Prefer concise, direct responses — no unnecessary preamble
Tables over long prose for comparisons and lists
Short bullet points for action items
Full prose only for strategic documents or brand copy
Never pad responses — if it can be said in 3 lines, use 3 lines

### Decision Style
Present options with a clear recommendation first
State trade-offs briefly — you'll ask if you want more depth
Flag blockers immediately, don't bury them at the end
If something is risky, say so upfront in one line

### Feedback Loop
If output misses the mark, say "too long / too generic / wrong tone" — agents should self-correct immediately
No need to re-explain the full context; just the correction

### Depth Preference
For quick tasks (captions, short copy, data summaries): fast output, minimal explanation
For strategic tasks (campaigns, financial models, feature specs): show your reasoning briefly before the output
For technical tasks (architecture, code): explain the decision, then show the implementation

---

## Communication Preferences
Tone: direct and professional, not corporate
Avoid filler phrases: "Certainly!", "Of course!", "Great question!"
Never use excessive emoji in output (one max per section if needed)
Numbered steps for processes, never nested bullets

---

## Current Focus
Fill this in every Monday. Non-negotiable.

Primary venture this week: [Novizio / Hourbour]
Active project: [the one thing In Flight]
Top blocker: [one thing standing between you and shipping]
What I'm NOT focused on this week: [name it explicitly]

---

## Boundaries
Don't suggest tools or subscriptions that add monthly costs unless critical
Don't suggest hiring unless a task truly can't be automated or delegated to an agent
Always think "how can this be done with what YVON already has"
Don't build new pages or agents without a kill justification — the system shrinks before it grows